 Responsibilities:

 Proven Success driving product development from concept to shipping; 



 Gather and organize requirements through customer feedback, bug bash, and demos and come up with plans to continuously improve metrics [monthly/quarterly/annually]; 



 Define product strategy and roadmap, and regularly update to the senior leadership team; 



 Analyze product data daily and recommend new systems, procedures, or product changes to improve efficiency as needed; 



 Thoroughly document release notes to accompany each sprint release. 



 Deliver project outcomes on-time and on-budget:

 Collaborate with Engineering to define the Execution Schedule and keep updated daily/weekly; 



 Utilize Asana platform to organize the project/communicate daily progress updates; 



 Define and track weekly key success metrics 



 Coordinate with designers, developers, and other key stakeholders: 



 Promote product perspectives within various teams and serve as the glue binding various stakeholder to a common goal; 



 Analyze key metrics and consult with managers, designers, and developers within X days to ensure changes are working as intended; 



 Liaise with the QA team to ensuring acceptance criteria is set for tickets to accommodate automated and manual testing; 



 Manage ongoing limited client communications and share status updates with key stakeholders. 



 Provide coaching/motivation/organization to project teams using Agile/Scrum: 



 Champion the insight of our customers and market in weekly meetings; 



 Effectively facilitate Scrum ceremonies, sprint planning, standups, story review, and retrospectives every biweekly sprint; 



 Build a trusting and safe environment where issues and problems can be discussed without fear of blame, retribution, or being judged. 



 Be a team player and embody Polymaths’ culture and core values always: 



 Bring a mindset of personal/professional development, continuous learning, and coaching to management of the Polymath team; 



 Embody initiative (go above and beyond the call of duty), respect for colleagues, resilience, and flexibility ongoingly; 



 Demonstrate razor-sharp execution and eagerness for perfection; 



 Willingness to learn new things fast. 



